SIMPLE: impetuous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impetuous
<hw>Im*pet"u*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>impetueux</ets>, L. <ets>impetuosus</ets>. See
<er>Impetus</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Rushing with force and
violence; moving with impetus; furious; forcible; violent; <as>as, an
<ex>impetuous</ex> wind; an <ex>impetuous</ex> torrent.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Went pouring forward with <qex>impetuous</qex> speed.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Vehement in feeling; hasty; passionate; violent;
<as>as, a man of <ex>impetuous</ex> temper</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The people, on their holidays,⟦br⟧
<qex>Impetuous</qex>, insolent, unquenchable.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Forcible; rapid; hasty; precipitate; furious;
boisterous; violent; raging; fierce; passionate.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Im*pet"u*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Im*pet"u*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impetus</ent>⟦br⟧
